    "The proposal is being read as architecturally sound and merely under-scaled, but the stronger adversarial reading is that the Rs 5 Cr ticket has been sized against the cadence of fresh inflow rather than against the architecture it claims to correct. A debt sleeve that leaves equity 8.5pp above the ceiling and debt 7.3pp below the floor is not a partial fix awaiting future tranches; it is a deployment that ratifies the residual breach by treating mandate compliance as a multi-year project rather than a current obligation. G1's requires_clarification on two simultaneous band gaps is the structural signal: the architecture being chosen is one in which the mandate band functions as a soft guideline subordinate to the deliberate non-action on the Reliance concentration, and the committee should name that choice rather than absorb it into the silent premise of the proposal.",
